# Lychee Link Checker Ignore Patterns
# Patterns in this file will be ignored by the link checker

# Exclude local/private URLs
http://localhost*
http://127.0.0.1*
http://0.0.0.0*

# Exclude URLs that require authentication
https://github.com/*/settings/*
https://github.com/*/new/*

# Exclude URLs that commonly rate limit or block bots
# (These can be manually checked periodically)
https://www.linkedin.com/*
https://twitter.com/*
https://x.com/*

# Bot-protected hosts that return 403/503 to automated checkers but are
# verified live in a browser. Excluded to keep the weekly external report
# actionable (signal, not noise). NOTE: scoped to infrastructure and
# first-party domains only — third-party/personal author sites are left in
# so genuine link rot still surfaces for human review.
https://docs.astro.build/*
https://www.digitalocean.com/*
https://www.hetzner.com/*
https://upcloud.com/*
https://mise.jdx.dev/*
https://creativecommons.org/*
https://onetimesecret.com/*
https://*.onetimesecret.com/*

# Exclude placeholder/example URLs
https://example.com/*
https://yourdomain.com/*
https://yourbrand.com/*
https://secrets.yourdomain.com
https://*.yourdomain.com
http://*.yourdomain.com

# Exclude URLs that might be in code examples but not real
mailto:*

# Exclude static asset paths (served from public/ at runtime, not in content dir)
.*/img/.*
.*/socialcards/.*

# Interactive demo / artifact pages live in src/pages, not src/content/docs, so
# the source-rooted internal link check (--root-dir src/content/docs) can't
# resolve them. They build to /artifacts/... in dist and are verified in the
# browser; documentation pages link to them (e.g. the SSO demos).
.*/artifacts/.*

# Exclude missing translations/guide pages (only en and zh-cn have this file;
# other locale index pages link to it but the pages don't exist yet)
.*/translations/guide$

# Self-hosting sub-pages (only exist in en; Starlight serves English
# fallback with "untranslated content" banner for other locales)
.*/self-hosting/configuration$
.*/self-hosting/getting-started$
.*/self-hosting/installation$

# REST API v2 docs (only exist in en)
.*/rest-api/v2$

# Note: The internal link check uses --root-dir src/content/docs with
# --fallback-extensions md,mdoc so that root-relative content paths
# (like /en/regions/) resolve correctly in offline mode.
